  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Radiation Plus Concurrent Nimotuzumab in Elderly Patients With Locoregionally Advanced
      Nasopharyngeal Carcinoma
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Elderly patients with locoregionally advanced nasopharyngeal carcinoma were given an initial
      dose of nimotuzumab (200 mg) 7days before receiving concurrent radiotherapy, weekly
      nimotuzumab (200 mg/week).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
